#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:185
msgid ""
"<placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> In this case the RPM update "
"automatically restores the old configuration files and sets file permissions."
msgstr ""
"<placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> В этом случае обновление из RPM "
"автоматически восстанавливает старые конфигурационные файлы и устанавливает "
"нужные права на файлы."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:195
msgid "Step 5: Check needed Perl modules"
msgstr "Шаг 5: Проверка требуемых Perl модулей"

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:200
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.CheckModules.pl\n"
msgstr "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.CheckModules.pl\n"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:198
msgid ""
"Verify that all needed Perl modules are installed on your system and install "
"any modules that might be missing.  <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:207
msgid "Step 6: Apply the database changes"
msgstr "Шаг 6: Применение обновлений базы данных"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:210
msgid "Step 6.1: Database schema update"
msgstr "Шаг 6.1: Схема обновления БД"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:213
msgid "MySQL:"
msgstr "MySQL:"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:217
msgid ""
"Note: new tables created in the MySQL UPGRADING process will be created with "
"the default table storage engine set in your MySQL server.  In MySQL 5.5 the "
"new default type is <literal>InnoDB</literal>.  If existing tables, e.g. "
"\"users\", have the table storage engine e.g. <literal>MyISAM</literal>, "
"then an error will be displayed when creating the foreign key constraints.  "
"In this case we recommend to switch all tables to <literal>InnoDB</literal> "
"with the console command <command>bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::Database::"
"MySQL::InnoDBMigration</command>."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:231
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> cd /opt/otrs/\n"
"shell> cat scripts/DBUpdate-to-5.mysql.sql | mysql -p -f -u root otrs\n"
"shell> bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::Database::Check\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:228
msgid ""
"Any problems with regards to the storage engine will be reported by the "
"<filename>bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::Database::Check</filename> command, so "
"please run it to check for possible issues.  <placeholder type=\"screen\" id="
"\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:241
msgid "PostgreSQL:"
msgstr "PostgreSQL:"

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:244
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> cd /opt/otrs/\n"
"shell> cat scripts/DBUpdate-to-5.postgresql.sql | psql --set ON_ERROR_STOP=on --single-transaction otrs otrs\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:253
msgid "Step 6.2: Database migration script"
msgstr "Шаг 6.2: Скрипт миграции БД"

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:258
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> scripts/DBUpdate-to-5.pl\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:256
msgid ""
"Run the migration script (as user <code>otrs</code>, NOT as <code>root</"
"code>): <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> Do not continue the "
"upgrading process if this script did not work properly for you.  Otherwise "
"data loss may occur."
msgstr ""
"Выполните скрипт для миграции (как пользователь <code>otrs</code>, НЕ как  "
"<code>root</code>): <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> Не продолжайте "
"процесс обновления, если этот скрипт отрабатывает неправильно, по вашему "
"мнению. Иначе, вы можете потерять данные."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:269
msgid "Step 7: Refresh the configuration cache and delete caches"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:274
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> cd /opt/otrs/\n"
"shell> bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::Config::Rebuild\n"
"shell> bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::Cache::Delete\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:272
msgid ""
"Please run (as user <code>otrs</code>, <emphasis>not</emphasis> as "
"<code>root</code>): <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""
" Выполните (как пользователь <code>otrs</code>, <emphasis>не</emphasis> как "
"<code>root</code>): <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:283
msgid "Step 8: Restart your services"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:288
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> /etc/init.d/apache start\n"
"shell> /etc/init.d/postfix start\n"
"shell> /etc/init.d/cron start\n"
msgstr ""
"shell> /etc/init.d/apache start\n"
"shell> /etc/init.d/postfix start\n"
"shell> /etc/init.d/cron start\n"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:286
msgid ""
"e. g. (depends on used services): <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> "
"Now you can log into your system."
msgstr ""
"в т.ч. (зависящие от использующихся услуг): <placeholder type=\"screen\" id="
"\"0\"/> Теперь вы можете войти в систему."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:299
msgid "Step 9: Check installed packages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:303
msgid ""
"The OTRS packages of 4 are NOT compatible with OTRS 5, so you have to "
"perform a package upgrade!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:307
msgid ""
"The following packages are automatically uninstalled after the upgrade "
"process (if they where installed before):"
msgstr ""
"Следующие пакеты будут автоматически деинсталлированы после процесса "
"обновления (если были установлены ранее):"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:310
msgid "OTRSGenericInterfaceMappingXSLT"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:316
msgid "Step 10: Configure NodeIDs (only for multi-frontend clustered setups)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:320
msgid ""
"This step is only needed if you have a clustered setup with several frontend "
"machines."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:330
#, no-wrap
msgid "$Self->{'NodeID'} =  '2';   # assign a unique value for every frontend server\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:324
msgid ""
"From OTRS 5 on, every frontend server needs to have its own unique "
"<literal>NodeID</literal>.  This defaults to <literal>1</literal> and thus "
"does not need to be configured for single-frontend setups. If you have more "
"than one machine, each machine needs to have this value set to a unique "
"value between <literal>1</literal> and <literal>999</literal>. This "
"configuration needs to be done in the file <filename>Kernel/Config.pm</"
"filename>: <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:337
msgid "Step 11: Check follow-up detection configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:340
msgid ""
"The follow-up detection settings were reorganized. Now OTRS searches by "
"default in email subject and references to detect follow-ups. Please check "
"in AdminSysConfig <literal>Ticket</literal> -&gt; <literal>Core::PostMaster</"
"literal> if you need to make any changes to the follow-up detection "
"configuration (for example to search in body, attachments or raw email "
"content)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:349
msgid "Step 12: Start the OTRS Daemon"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:357
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:315
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.Daemon.pl start\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:352
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:310
msgid ""
"The new OTRS daemon is responsible for handling any asynchronous and "
"recurring tasks in OTRS.  What has been in cron file definitions previously "
"is now handled by the OTRS daemon, which is now required to operate OTRS. "
"The daemon also handles all GenericAgent jobs and must be started from the "
"<literal>otrs</literal> user.  <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:365
msgid "Step 13: Update and activate cron jobs"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:372
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:329
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> cd /opt/otrs/var/cron\n"
"shell> for foo in *.dist; do cp $foo `basename $foo .dist`; done\n"
msgstr ""
"shell> cd /opt/otrs/var/cron\n"
"shell> for foo in *.dist; do cp $foo `basename $foo .dist`; done\n"

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:380
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:337
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/Cron.sh start\n"
msgstr "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/Cron.sh start\n"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:368
msgid ""
"There are two default OTRS cron files in <filename>/opt/otrs/var/cron/*."
"dist</filename>, and their purpose is to make sure that the OTRS Daemon is "
"running.  They need to be activated by copying them without the \".dist\" "
"filename extension.  <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> To schedule "
"these cron jobs on your system, you can use the script <filename>Cron.sh</"
"filename> with the <literal>otrs</literal> user.  <placeholder type=\"screen"
"\" id=\"1\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:385
msgid ""
"Please note that if you had any custom cron jobs, you should consider moving "
"them to SysConfig (<literal>Daemon</literal> -&gt; <literal>Daemon::"
"SchedulerCronTaskManager::Task</literal>)  to have them executed by the OTRS "
"daemon as well.  You might also need to adapt your custom scripts, because "
"now most OTRS commands are managed by <filename>bin/otrs.Console.pl</"
"filename> instead of single scripts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:394
msgid "Step 14: Review your ticket notifications"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:396
msgid ""
"With OTRS 5 ticket notifications are configured differently than in previous "
"versions.  They are now part of the \"Event Notifications\" that were "
"previously available as well (now called just \"Ticket Notifications\"). "
"Your existing ticket notifications have been migrated into the list of "
"ticket notifications, but deactivated. You have also received the new "
"default ticket notifications, active by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:403
msgid ""
"In case you did not modify the old ticket notifications you don't have to do "
"anything. If you have made local modifications or translations, you have two "
"choices: a) you can migrate your modifications to the new ticket "
"notifications (recommended) or b) you can deactivate the new notifications "
"and activate the old notifications again."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:409
msgid ""
"Please also review the escalation notification recipient settings and see if "
"they match with your expectations (agents who have the ticket in one of "
"their custom queues vs. all agents with read permissions).  This was "
"configured via a setting in the file <filename>Kernel/Config/GenericAgent."
"pm</filename> (now obsolete) previously and can now be controlled via the "
"GUI for each notification separately."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:415
msgid "Step 15: Update system registration (optional)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:417
msgid ""
"If the system is already registered with OTRS Group, it is strongly "
"recommended to update the registration information at this time. This will "
"update the registered version of the system (among other changes) in the "
"OTRS Group records, in order to get much accurate information from the cloud "
"services."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:423
msgid ""
"If you don't update the registration information manually, it will be done "
"automatically on a regular basis, but this could happen some hours or days "
"after. During this period it might be possible to get wrong information from "
"cloud services like <emphasis role=\"bold\">OTRS Business Solution™</"
"emphasis> updates."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:429
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> cd /opt/otrs/\n"
"shell> bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::Registration::UpdateSend --force\n"
"shell> bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::Cache::Delete\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:438
msgid "Step 16: Migrate custom Perl based GenericAgent jobs (optional)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:440
msgid ""
"This is only relevant if you had any custom GenericAgent jobs in Perl OTRS 4 "
"configuration files such as <filename>Kernel/Config/GenericAgent.pm</"
"filename> that cannot be handled with the regular ticket notifications.  "
"Such jobs now need to be registered as OTRS Daemon cron tasks in the "
"SysConfig (<literal>Daemon</literal> -&gt; <literal>Daemon::"
"SchedulerCronTaskManager::Task</literal>), in order to be executed on a "
"regular basis."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:447
msgid ""
"There are 5 settings in the SysConfig prepared for this purpose "
"(<literal>Daemon::SchedulerCronTaskManager::Task###GenericAgentFile1</"
"literal> to <literal>Daemon::SchedulerCronTaskManager::"
"Task###GenericAgentFile5</literal>).  If more settings are needed they can "
"be added in a custom SysConfig setting file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:453
msgid ""
"Please replace \"&lt;ModuleName&gt;\" with the file that contains the custom "
"GenericAgent jobs configuration, e.g. <literal>Kernel::Config::GenericAgent</"
"literal> for the file: <filename>Kernel/Config/GenericAgent.pm</filename>, "
"set the schedule to match the periodicity as it was executed before, mark "
"the setting as active and save the changes."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:462
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::GenericAgent::Run --help\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:460
msgid ""
"To get more information about other parameters that can be used while "
"running the GenericAgent jobs, please execute: <placeholder type=\"screen\" "
"id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:470
msgid "Step 17: Setup bash autocompletion (optional)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:472
msgid ""
"All regular OTRS command line operations now happen via the OTRS Console "
"interface <filename>bin/otrs.Console.pl</filename>. This provides an auto "
"completion for the bash shell which makes finding the right command and "
"options much easier."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:477
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:357
msgid ""
"You can activate the bash autocompletion by installing the package "
"<literal>bash-completion</literal>.  It will automatically detect and load "
"the file <filename>/opt/otrs/.bash_completion</filename> for the "
"<literal>otrs</literal> user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:481
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:361
msgid ""
"After restarting your shell, you can just type <filename>bin/otrs.Console."
"pl</filename> followed by TAB, and it will list all available commands. If "
"you type a few characters of the command name, TAB will show all matching "
"commands. After typing a complete command, all possible options and "
"arguments will be shown by pressing TAB."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:489
msgid "Step 18: Review ticket action screen configurations (optional)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:491
msgid ""
"Some ticket action screens like \"Note\" had default subjects in OTRS 4 "
"(configurable via SysConfig, <literal>Ticket::Frontend::"
"AgentTicketNote###Subject</literal> in this case). These default subjects "
"have been removed to reduce the amount of potentially redundant/meaningless "
"data. You might want to re-add them if they are mandatory for you."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/upgrading.xml:499
msgid "Step 19: Well done!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:6
msgid "The Simple Way - Installation of Pre-Built Packages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:9
msgid ""
"If available for your platform you should use pre-built packages to install "
"OTRS, since it is the simplest and most convenient method.  You can find "
"them in the download area at <ulink url=\"https://www.otrs.com/download-open-"
"source-help-desk-software-otrs-free/\">www.otrs.com</ulink>.  The following "
"sections describe the installation of OTRS with a pre-built or binary "
"package on SUSE and Red Hat systems.  Only if you are unable to use the pre-"
"built packages for some reason should you follow the manual process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:16
msgid "Installing the RPM on a SUSE Linux server"
msgstr "Установка из rpm-пакетов на сервер под управлением Suse Linux"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:19
msgid ""
"This section describes the installation of our RPM package on a SUSE Linux "
"server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:23
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:179
msgid "Preparing the database for OTRS"
msgstr "Подготовка базы данных для OTRS"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:26
msgid ""
"You can use OTRS using different database back-ends: <application>MySQL</"
"application>, <application>PostgreSQL</application> or <application>Oracle</"
"application>. The most popular database to deploy OTRS on is MySQL.  This "
"chapter shows the steps you need to take to configure MySQL on a SUSE-based "
"server. Of course you can install the database on a dedicated database "
"server if needed for scalability or other purposes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:32
msgid ""
"If you follow this chapter on openSUSE 12.3 and up you'll actually not "
"install <application>MySQL</application> but <application>MariaDB</"
"application> instead, a MySQL compatible fork of the MySQL code. This is no "
"problem, it will work just as well (and even a little better at some points)."
msgstr ""
"Если вы следуете описанному в этой главе на openSUSE 12.3 и еще не "
"установили <application>MySQL</application> но вместо нее можно установить "
"<application>MariaDB</application> , известный форк/ветку MySQL. Проблем не "
"будет, все будет работать нормально (даже немного лучше в некоторых "
"аспектах)."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:37
msgid "Install MySQL by executing the following command as root:"
msgstr ""
"Установите MySQL с использованием следующей команды с правами пользователя "
"root:"

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "linux:~ # zypper install mysql perl-DBD-mysql\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:49
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:197
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:287
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"max_allowed_packet   = 20M\n"
"query_cache_size     = 32M\n"
"innodb_log_file_size = 256M\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:47
msgid ""
"This will install MySQL with the default options on your system. You'll need "
"to change the defaults in order to make it suitable for OTRS. With a text "
"editor open the file <filename>/etc/my.cnf</filename> and add following "
"lines under the [mysqld] section: <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:57
msgid ""
"Now execute <command>systemctl restart mysql.service</command> to re-start "
"the database server and activate these changes. Then run <command>/usr/bin/"
"mysql_secure_installation</command> and follow the on-screen instructions to "
"set a database root password, remove anonymous access and remove the test "
"database. Lastly, run <command>systemctl enable mysql.service</command> in "
"order to make sure MySQL is automatically started at server startup time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:66
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:213
msgid "Installing OTRS"
msgstr "Установка OTRS"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:68
msgid ""
"Install OTRS with via the command line using <command>zypper</command>. This "
"will also pull in some dependencies such as the Apache web server and some "
"Perl modules. Make sure you copied the OTRS RPM file to the current "
"directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:72
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"otrs-sles:~ # zypper install otrs*.rpm\n"
"....\n"
"Retrieving package otrs-x.x.x-01.noarch (1/26), 17.5 MiB (74.3 MiB unpacked)\n"
"Installing: otrs-x.x.x-01 [done]\n"
"Additional rpm output:\n"
"Check OTRS user ... otrs added.\n"
"\n"
"...\n"
"\n"
"otrs-sles:~ #\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:72
msgid ""
"<placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> Now restart Apache with the command "
"<command>systemctl restart apache2.service</command> to load the "
"configuration changes for OTRS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:91
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:268
msgid "Installation of additional perl modules"
msgstr "Установка дополнительных perl модулей"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/packages.xml:92
msgid ""
"OTRS needs some more modules than can be installed by the RPM. You can post-"
